</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="149" type="remarks">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="149">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="149">
According to the original descriptions, three of the diagnostic generic characters of the genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bethune-Baker" authorityYear="1908" class="Insecta" family="Limacodidae" genus="Squamosa" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Squamosa" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="149" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="149">Squamosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are: the antennae bipectinated only at the basal half in males, the valva without saccular process, and the juxta with lateral asymmetrical processes (
<bibRefCitation author="Solovyev, AV" journalOrPublisher="Zootaxa" pageId="0" pageNumber="149" refId="B9" refString="Solovyev, AV, Witt, ThJ, 2009. The Limacodidae of Vietnam. Entomofauna (Supplement No. 16): 33-229." title="The Limacodidae of Vietnam. Entomofauna (Supplement No. 16): 33 - 229." year="2009">Solovyev and Witt 2009</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Wu, CS" journalOrPublisher="Dong Wu Fen Lei Xue Bao" pageId="0" pageNumber="149" pagination="237 - 240" refId="B10" refString="Wu, CS, Fang, CL, 2009. A review of the genus Squamosa Bethune-Baker in China (Lepidoptera: Limacodidae). Dong Wu Fen Lei Xue Bao 34 (2): 237 - 240" title="A review of the genus Squamosa Bethune-Baker in China (Lepidoptera: Limacodidae)." volume="34" year="2009">Wu and Fang 2009</bibRefCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Wu &amp; Solovyev &amp; Han" authorityYear="2022" class="Insecta" family="Limacodidae" genus="Squamosa" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Squamosa medogensis" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="149" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="medogensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="149">Squamosa medogensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. nov. does not match any of the above three characters, but since all other typical characters for this genus were observed, we therefore tentatively place this new species in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bethune-Baker" authorityYear="1908" class="Insecta" family="Limacodidae" genus="Squamosa" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Squamosa" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="149" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="149">Squamosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
